# Great CTO — AI engineering management contract for Cursor

# Generated by `npx great-cto adapt --platform cursor`. The full agent
# contract lives in AGENTS.md (also generated). This file is the Cursor-
# native subset focusing on inline-completion and chat behaviour.

archetype: <auto-detected>     # one of 25: web-service / fintech / commerce / healthcare / mlops / agent-product / edtech / gov-public / insurance / etc.
compliance: <auto-attached>    # gates derived from archetype: pci-dss / gdpr / hipaa / sox / kyc-aml / coppa / fedramp / nist-800-53 / etc.

## Behaviour

Before suggesting code changes:
- Read AGENTS.md for repo-wide conventions
- Read .great_cto/PROJECT.md for archetype constraints (if present)
- Check ~/.great_cto/decisions.md for prior ADRs on the topic — solved problems should stay solved
- Cross-project lessons live in ~/.great_cto/lessons.md (promoted via /crystallize after 3+ occurrences)

Before merging:
- Run `npx great-cto ci` locally — same gate as CI, exits 1 on critical findings
- The CI auto-detects $GITHUB_ACTIONS and emits inline ::error:: annotations on PR diffs
- SARIF output uploads to GitHub Security tab via codeql-action/upload-sarif

## Gates that block merges (do not bypass)

- security-officer: any change touching auth, payments, PII
- qa-engineer: any feature merge
- performance-engineer: any change to hot path
- db-migration-reviewer: any migrations/ change

Override only with `/waiver <gate> <reason>`. Auto-expires in 14 days.

## Style

- TDD: tests RED → implementation GREEN → refactor (80%+ coverage default)
- Conventional commits: feat / fix / docs / refactor / test / chore
- One concern per PR — refactors and behaviour changes are separate PRs
- No secrets in code (`great-cto scan` blocks 13+ secret patterns by default)
- No prompt injection: don't concatenate user input into system prompt template literals

## MCP integration

This repo is also configured for `great-cto mcp` — Cursor's chat panel can call:
- `scan` — 24 OWASP LLM Top 10 rules (prompt-injection / secrets / SSRF / RAG / cost-runaway)
- `list_rules` — full catalogue
- `detect_archetype` — archetype + compliance for any path
- `estimate_cost` — LLM-agent time + cost vs human-team equivalent
- `query_decisions` — search ~/.great_cto/decisions.md ADR log

Add to .cursor/mcp.json:
```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "great-cto": { "command": "npx", "args": ["-y", "great-cto@latest", "mcp"] }
  }
}
```

## Out of scope

Do not invent business decisions. If the spec is ambiguous, ask. Do not skip
gates "because it's just a small change" — that's the path to incidents.
After any P0 incident, append to .great_cto/lessons.md.
